<blockquote>
<p>As the name implies, <code v-pre>redirect</code> a plug-in is <code v-pre>uri</code> a redirection and redirection of.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="redirect" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#redirect"><span>Redirect</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li>When we <code v-pre>Rule</code> configure the custom path, it should be a reachable service path.</li>
<li>When the request is matched, the service jump will be performed <code v-pre>308</code> according to the user-defined path <code v-pre>Soul gateway</code>.</li>
</ul>
<figure><img src="https://dromara.org/img/soul/plugin/redirect/redirect-01.png" alt="Redirect configuration" tabindex="0"><figcaption>Redirect configuration</figcaption></figure>
<h3 id="gateway-self-interface-forwarding" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#gateway-self-interface-forwarding"><span>Gateway self-interface forwarding</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li>When the matching rules are met, the service internally forwards using <code v-pre>DispatcherHandler</code> the internal interface.</li>
<li>To realize the gateway's own interface forwarding, we need to start with the prefix in the configuration path <code v-pre>/</code>. The specific configuration is shown in the following figure.</li>
</ul>
<figure><img src="https://dromara.org/img/soul/plugin/redirect/redirect-02.png" alt="Self-interface forwarding" tabindex="0"><figcaption>Self-interface forwarding</figcaption></figure>
<h2 id="source-code-parsing" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#source-code-parsing"><span>Source Code Parsing</span></a></h2>
